hpicfIpDhcpSnoop.name: hpicfIpDhcpSnoop

revisions.description: Added objects hpicfDhcpSnoopClearBindings, hpicfDhcpSnoopClearBindingsIpType, hpicfDhcpSnoopClearBindingsIpAddr, hpicfDhcpSnoopClearBindingsPort, hpicfDhcpSnoopClearBindingsVlan. Also added group hpicfDhcpSnoopClearBindingsOptionsGroup and compliance hpicfDhcpSnoopCompliance10.
Added object hpicfDhcpSnoopAllowOverwriteBinding. Added group hpicfDhcpSnoopAllowOverwriteBindingGroup and compliance hpicfDhcpSnoopCompliance9.
Added object hpicfDhcpSnoopClearStats.Added group hpicfDhcpSnoopClearStatsOptionsGroup and compliance hpicfDhcpSnoopClearStatsCompliance.

Added MIB objects hpicfDhcpSnoopPortMaxbind, hpicfDhcpSnoopPortStaticBinding, hpicfDhcpSnoopPortDynamicBinding and hpicfDhcpSnoopMaxbindPktsDropped for Max-Bindings , Created groups hpicfDhcpSnoopPktsGroup1 and hpicfDhcpSnoopMaxbindingGroup and Compliances hpicfDhcpSnoopCompliance6 and hpicfDhcpSnoopCompliance7 added.
Added hpicfDhcpSnoopPktsSent, hpicfDhcpSnoopPktsReceived, hpicfDhcpSnoopPktsDropped, Group hpicfDhcpSnoopPktsGroup and Compliance hpicfDhcpSnoopCompliance4.
Add support for static IP address bindings.

hpicfIpDhcpSnoop.contactinfo: Hewlett-Packard Company 8000 Foothills Blvd. Roseville, CA 95747
hpicfIpDhcpSnoop.description: This MIB module contains HP proprietary objects for managing DHCP Snooping.

hpicfDhcpSnoopErrantReply.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopErrantReply
hpicfDhcpSnoopErrantReply.description: An hpicfDhcpSnoopErrantReply notification signifies that the DHCP snooping entity has detected and dropped an errant DHCP response packet.

hpicfDhcpSnoopEnable.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopEnable
hpicfDhcpSnoopEnable.description: The administrative status of the DHCP Snooping feature.

hpicfDhcpSnoopVlanEnable.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopVlanEnable
hpicfDhcpSnoopVlanEnable.description: The administrative status for DHCP Snooping on each VLAN. There will be one bit in this string for each possible VLAN ID. Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight VLANs, with the first octet specifying VLAN IDs 1 through 8, the second octet specifying VLAN IDs 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered VLAN ID, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered VLAN ID. Thus, each possible VLAN ID of the bridge is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If a bit at position 'n' has a value of '1', then DHCP Snooping is enabled on VLAN 'n'. If this bit has a value of '0',DHCP Snooping is not enabled on the VLAN 'n',

hpicfDhcpSnoopVerifyMac.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopVerifyMac
hpicfDhcpSnoopVerifyMac.description: When this variable is set to 'true', DHCP Snooping will verify that the MAC address in the chaddr field of the DHCP header matches the source MAC address in all DHCP packets received on untrusted ports. When this variable is set to 'false', DHCP Snooping will omit this check. The value of this variable is ignored when DHCP Snooping is disabled.

hpicfDhcpSnoopDatabaseFile.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopDatabaseFile
hpicfDhcpSnoopDatabaseFile.description: A location to store the lease database, or to retrieve it after a reboot. The location must be given in the form of a Uniform Resource Locator (URL) as defined in RFC 2396. The allowed character sets and the encoding rules defined in RFC 2396 section 2 apply.

hpicfDhcpSnoopDatabaseWriteDelay.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopDatabaseWriteDelay
hpicfDhcpSnoopDatabaseWriteDelay.description: The number of seconds to delay writing the DHCP lease database file after a database change. This potentially allows grouping multiple database changes into a single write. The default is 300 seconds.

hpicfDhcpSnoopDatabaseWriteTimeout.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopDatabaseWriteTimeout
hpicfDhcpSnoopDatabaseWriteTimeout.description: The number of seconds to wait for the database file transfer to finish before giving up and declaring a failure. A value of 0 means continue retrying indefinitely. The default is 300 seconds.

hpicfDhcpSnoopOpt82Insert.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopOpt82Insert
hpicfDhcpSnoopOpt82Insert.description: When this object is set to true, DHCP snooping will add a DHCP relay information option to DHCP client packets that it forwards on trusted ports, and will examine and strip DHCP relay information options that were inserted by this switch on DHCP server packets that it forwards to untrusted ports. Note that when DHCP relay and DHCP snooping are both enabled, and this object is set to true, relay information option processing will be handled by DHCP snooping, and any DHCP relay settings for relay information option processing will be ignored. This object defaults to true.

hpicfDhcpSnoopOpt82Policy.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopOpt82Policy
hpicfDhcpSnoopOpt82Policy.description: This object configures the behavior of DHCP snooping when forwarding a DHCP packet from an untrusted port that already has a DHCP relay information option present. The policies supported are: keep - forward the packet without updating the existing option replace - replace the existing option with one generated by this switch drop - drop the packet This policy is only applied if DHCP snooping is enabled and hpicfDhcpSnoopOpt82Insert is true. In all cases where this policy is applied, if there is no relay information option present in the received packet, DHCP snooping will add one. The default policy is drop.

hpicfDhcpSnoopOpt82RemoteId.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopOpt82RemoteId
hpicfDhcpSnoopOpt82RemoteId.description: This object configures the value that will be used for the remote ID sub-option of the relay information that will be inserted by DHCP snooping. The possible values are: mac - switch MAC address, subnetIP - switch IP address on the VLAN on which the DHCP packet was received, mgmtIP - switch IP address on the management VLAN. The value of this object is ignored unless DHCP snooping is enabled and hpicfDhcpSnoopOpt82Insert is true. The default value is mac.

hpicfDhcpSnoopErrantReplyEnable.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopErrantReplyEnable
hpicfDhcpSnoopErrantReplyEnable.description: The operational status of hpicfDhcpSnoopErrantReply notifications. The default value is 1 (Enabled). A value of 2 represents Disabled. Writing this object requires authentication, such as provided by SNMPv3.

hpicfDhcpSnoopDatabaseFTPort.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopDatabaseFTPort
hpicfDhcpSnoopDatabaseFTPort.description: A location to store the port value of the FT Server. The default port value will be 69 for TFTP and 22 for SFTP.

hpicfDhcpSnoopDatabaseSFTPUsername.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopDatabaseSFTPUsername
hpicfDhcpSnoopDatabaseSFTPUsername.description: A location to store the Username of the SFTP Server. The default value of username is root.

hpicfDhcpSnoopDatabaseSFTPPassword.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopDatabaseSFTPPassword
hpicfDhcpSnoopDatabaseSFTPPassword.description: A location to store the Password of the SFTP Server

hpicfDhcpSnoopDatabaseValidateSFTPServer.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopDatabaseValidateSFTPServer
hpicfDhcpSnoopDatabaseValidateSFTPServer.description: This object sets the validate-sftp-server flag. When enabled, the user must login to the SFTP server to verify and accept the public key of the server. When disabled, the public key is accepted automatically.

hpicfDhcpSnoopAllowOverwriteBinding.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopAllowOverwriteBinding
hpicfDhcpSnoopAllowOverwriteBinding.description: When set to true, allows DHCP Snooping binding to be overwritten for the same IP address. When a DHCP server offers a host an IP address and if this address is already bound to an existing host in the binding table, the existing binding is overwritten for the new host if the new host is successfully able to acquire the same IP address. When false, the DHCP offer packet will be dropped.

hpicfDhcpSnoopPortEntry.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopPortEntry
hpicfDhcpSnoopPortEntry.description: DHCP snooping configuration information for a single port.

hpicfDhcpSnoopPortTrust.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopPortTrust
hpicfDhcpSnoopPortTrust.description: This object indicates whether this port is trusted for DHCP snooping.

hpicfDhcpSnoopPortMaxbind.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopPortMaxbind
hpicfDhcpSnoopPortMaxbind.description: This object indicates the maximum number of bindings allowed on a port.

hpicfDhcpSnoopPortStaticBinding.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopPortStaticBinding
hpicfDhcpSnoopPortStaticBinding.description: This object indicates the static bindings present on a port.

hpicfDhcpSnoopPortDynamicBinding.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopPortDynamicBinding
hpicfDhcpSnoopPortDynamicBinding.description: This object indicates the Dynamic bindings present on a port.

hpicfDhcpSnoopServerTable.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopServerTable
hpicfDhcpSnoopServerTable.description: Table of authorized DHCP server addresses.

hpicfDhcpSnoopServerEntry.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopServerEntry
hpicfDhcpSnoopServerEntry.description: A row in the table, containing the address of a single authorized DHCP server.

hpicfDhcpSnoopServerAddrType.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopServerAddrType
hpicfDhcpSnoopServerAddrType.description: The type of address in hpicfDhcpSnoopServerAddress.

hpicfDhcpSnoopServerAddress.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopServerAddress
hpicfDhcpSnoopServerAddress.description: The address of a known valid DHCP server. The type of address contained in this object is indicated by hpicfDhcpSnoopServerAddrType. For DHCP snooping to allow a server to client packet to be forwarded, it must be received on a trusted port from a server address in this table. If this table is empty, all addresses are trusted. Note that this feature compares the source address of the received DHCP server packet against the addresses in this table. This means that this table needs to contain trusted server addresses as well as trusted DHCP relays that a server packet may be relayed through.

hpicfDhcpSnoopServerStatus.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopServerStatus
hpicfDhcpSnoopServerStatus.description: The status of this DHCP server address entry. Only 'active' entries are used when validating DHCP server packets.

hpicfIpStaticBindingsTable.name: hpicfIpStaticBindingsTable
hpicfIpStaticBindingsTable.description: A table of configured static IP address bindings for this device. Active rows in this table will also be reported in the hpicfDhcpSnoopBindingsTable as entries with an hpicfDhcpSnoopBindingsLeaseTime of 0xffffffff and an hpicfDhcpSnoopBindingsType of 'static'.

hpicfIpStaticBindingsEntry.name: hpicfIpStaticBindingsEntry
hpicfIpStaticBindingsEntry.description: A row in the table, containing a single static IP address binding.

hpicfIpStaticBindingsVlan.name: hpicfIpStaticBindingsVlan
hpicfIpStaticBindingsVlan.description: The VLAN ID on which this static address binding is valid.

hpicfIpStaticBindingsAddrType.name: hpicfIpStaticBindingsAddrType
hpicfIpStaticBindingsAddrType.description: The type of IP address contained in hpicfIpStaticBindingsAddress. The only values expected are ipv4 or ipv6.

hpicfIpStaticBindingsAddress.name: hpicfIpStaticBindingsAddress
hpicfIpStaticBindingsAddress.description: The static IP address of this binding. The type of address contained in this object is indicated by hpicfIpStaticBindingsAddrType.

hpicfIpStaticBindingsMacAddress.name: hpicfIpStaticBindingsMacAddress
hpicfIpStaticBindingsMacAddress.description: The MAC address associated with this static binding on this VLAN.

hpicfIpStaticBindingsInterface.name: hpicfIpStaticBindingsInterface
hpicfIpStaticBindingsInterface.description: The interface that this static IP address binding is valid on in this VLAN.

hpicfIpStaticBindingsStatus.name: hpicfIpStaticBindingsStatus
hpicfIpStaticBindingsStatus.description: The status of this static IP address binding. This object cannot be set to 'active' until valid value has been configured for hpicfIpStaticBindingsMacAddress and hpicfIpStaticBindingsInterface.

hpicfDhcpSnoopCSForwards.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopCSForwards
hpicfDhcpSnoopCSForwards.description: Number of snooped DHCP packets that were successfully forwarded from untrusted client ports towards trusted DHCP server ports.

hpicfDhcpSnoopCSMACMismatches.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopCSMACMismatches
hpicfDhcpSnoopCSMACMismatches.description: Number of snooped DHCP client packets that were discarded because the MAC source address of the packet did not match the chaddr.

hpicfDhcpSnoopCSUntrustedOpt82s.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopCSUntrustedOpt82s
hpicfDhcpSnoopCSUntrustedOpt82s.description: Number of snooped DHCP client packets that were discarded because they were received on an untrusted port and contained a relay information option.

hpicfDhcpSnoopCSBadReleases.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopCSBadReleases
hpicfDhcpSnoopCSBadReleases.description: Number of snooped DHCP client packets that were discarded because they were DHCPRELEASE or DHCPDECLINE packets received on a port different from the port that the address was leased to.

hpicfDhcpSnoopCSUntrustedDestPorts.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopCSUntrustedDestPorts
hpicfDhcpSnoopCSUntrustedDestPorts.description: Number of snooped DHCP client unicast packets that were dropped because they were destined to untrusted ports.

hpicfDhcpSnoopSCForwards.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopSCForwards
hpicfDhcpSnoopSCForwards.description: Number of snooped DHCP packets that were successfully forwarded from trusted DHCP server ports to untrusted client ports.

hpicfDhcpSnoopSCUntrustedPorts.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopSCUntrustedPorts
hpicfDhcpSnoopSCUntrustedPorts.description: Number of snooped DHCP server packets that were dropped because they were received from untrusted ports.

hpicfDhcpSnoopSCUntrustedServers.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopSCUntrustedServers
hpicfDhcpSnoopSCUntrustedServers.description: Number of snooped DHCP server packets that were dropped because they were received from unauthorized DHCP server addresses.

hpicfDhcpSnoopSCOpt82Failures.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopSCOpt82Failures
hpicfDhcpSnoopSCOpt82Failures.description: Number of snooped DHCP server packets that were dropped because they did not contain a valid relay information option.

hpicfDhcpSnoopDBFileWriteAttempts.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopDBFileWriteAttempts
hpicfDhcpSnoopDBFileWriteAttempts.description: Number of attempts that have been made to write the DHCP lease database to a configured file location.

hpicfDhcpSnoopDBFileWriteFailures.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopDBFileWriteFailures
hpicfDhcpSnoopDBFileWriteFailures.description: Number of times that an attempt to write the DHCP lease database to a configured file location has failed.

hpicfDhcpSnoopDBFileReadStatus.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopDBFileReadStatus
hpicfDhcpSnoopDBFileReadStatus.description: This object indicates whether we were able to successfully load the DHCP lease database from the configured location after the last reboot.

hpicfDhcpSnoopDBFileWriteStatus.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopDBFileWriteStatus
hpicfDhcpSnoopDBFileWriteStatus.description: This object indicates whether the DHCP lease database is currently synchronized with the the configured file server. 'notConfigured' means that we have not been configured with a server location. 'delaying' means that we are waiting for the write delay to expire before writing the current database. 'inProgress' means that a lease database transfer is active. 'succeeded' means that all leases in our database have been written to the server. 'failed' means that the last attempt to write our lease database failed.

hpicfDhcpSnoopDBFileLastWriteTime.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopDBFileLastWriteTime
hpicfDhcpSnoopDBFileLastWriteTime.description: The time that we last successfully wrote our lease database to the server. This object will contain a value of all zeroes if we have not written our lease database since the last reboot.

hpicfDhcpSnoopPktsSent.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopPktsSent
hpicfDhcpSnoopPktsSent.description: Total number of snooped DHCP packets that were successfully sent.

hpicfDhcpSnoopPktsReceived.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopPktsReceived
hpicfDhcpSnoopPktsReceived.description: Total number of snooped DHCP packets that were received.

hpicfDhcpSnoopPktsDropped.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopPktsDropped
hpicfDhcpSnoopPktsDropped.description: Total number of snooped DHCP packets that were dropped.

hpicfDhcpSnoopMaxbindPktsDropped.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopMaxbindPktsDropped
hpicfDhcpSnoopMaxbindPktsDropped.description: Total number of snooped DHCP packets that were dropped due to max-binding configuration.

hpicfDhcpSnoopBindingsTable.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopBindingsTable
hpicfDhcpSnoopBindingsTable.description: A table of DHCP bindings that have been learned by this device.

hpicfDhcpSnoopBindingsEntry.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopBindingsEntry
hpicfDhcpSnoopBindingsEntry.description: A row in the table, containing a single DHCP binding.

hpicfDhcpSnoopBindingsVlan.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopBindingsVlan
hpicfDhcpSnoopBindingsVlan.description: The VLAN ID on which this client binding was learned.

hpicfDhcpSnoopBindingsMacAddress.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopBindingsMacAddress
hpicfDhcpSnoopBindingsMacAddress.description: The MAC address of the DHCP client that this binding applies to.

hpicfDhcpSnoopBindingsAddrType.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopBindingsAddrType
hpicfDhcpSnoopBindingsAddrType.description: The type of IP address contained in hpicfDhcpSnoopBindingsAddress. The only values expected are ipv4 or ipv6.

hpicfDhcpSnoopBindingsAddress.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopBindingsAddress
hpicfDhcpSnoopBindingsAddress.description: An IP address that has been leased to this client. The type of address contained in this object is indicated by hpicfDhcpSnoopBindingsAddrType.

hpicfDhcpSnoopBindingsInterface.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopBindingsInterface
hpicfDhcpSnoopBindingsInterface.description: The interface that this DHCP client is connected to.

hpicfDhcpSnoopBindingsLeaseTime.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopBindingsLeaseTime
hpicfDhcpSnoopBindingsLeaseTime.description: The number of seconds remaining until this DHCP lease times out. A value of 0xffffffff indicates an infinite lease.

hpicfDhcpSnoopBindingsType.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopBindingsType
hpicfDhcpSnoopBindingsType.description: This object indicates how this binding was learned. A value of 'dhcp' indicates that this binding was learned by snooping a DHCP lease. A value of 'static' indicates that this binding was statically configured via the hpicfIpStaticBindingsTable.

hpicfDhcpSnoopBindingsSecVlan.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopBindingsSecVlan
hpicfDhcpSnoopBindingsSecVlan.description: The secondary VLAN on which this client binding was learned. If binding is learned on primary or normal VLAN, this object will be zero.

hpicfDhcpSnoopNotifyCount.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopNotifyCount
hpicfDhcpSnoopNotifyCount.description: A count of the DHCP snooping notification sent from the DHCP snooping entity to the SNMP entity. This count may be greater than the count of notifications actually transmitted by the SNMP entity due to rate limiting or configuration.

hpicfDhcpSnoopErrantSrcMAC.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopErrantSrcMAC
hpicfDhcpSnoopErrantSrcMAC.description: The MAC address received in the errant DHCP/BootP reply packet.

hpicfDhcpSnoopErrantSrcIPType.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopErrantSrcIPType
hpicfDhcpSnoopErrantSrcIPType.description: InetAddressType of the address reported in hpicfDhcpSnoopErrantSrcIP.

hpicfDhcpSnoopErrantSrcIP.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopErrantSrcIP
hpicfDhcpSnoopErrantSrcIP.description: The IP address received in the errant DHCP/BootP reply packet.

hpicfDhcpSnoopClearStats.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopClearStats
hpicfDhcpSnoopClearStats.description: When the value of this object is set to TRUE, all the dhcp-snoop statistics will be cleared. When the value of this object is set to FALSE, the operation is ignored. A get request for this object always returns FALSE.

hpicfDhcpSnoopClearBindings.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopClearBindings
hpicfDhcpSnoopClearBindings.description: When the value of this object is set to TRUE, all the dynamic DHCP Snooping binding entries will be cleared. A write operation of FALSE leads to no operation and a get request for this object will always return FALSE.

hpicfDhcpSnoopClearBindingsIpType.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopClearBindingsIpType
hpicfDhcpSnoopClearBindingsIpType.description: This object indicates the type of the IP address of the DHCP Snooping binding entry.

hpicfDhcpSnoopClearBindingsIpAddr.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopClearBindingsIpAddr
hpicfDhcpSnoopClearBindingsIpAddr.description: Clears the dynamic DHCP Snooping binding entry that matches with the given IP address. This object will always return 0.

hpicfDhcpSnoopClearBindingsPort.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopClearBindingsPort
hpicfDhcpSnoopClearBindingsPort.description: Clears all the dynamic DHCP Snooping binding entries that are associated with the given port. This object will always return 0.

hpicfDhcpSnoopClearBindingsVlan.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopClearBindingsVlan
hpicfDhcpSnoopClearBindingsVlan.description: Clears all the dynamic DHCP Snooping binding entries that match with the given VLAN. This object will always return 0.

hpicfDhcpSnoopBaseGroup.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopBaseGroup
hpicfDhcpSnoopBaseGroup.description: A collection of objects for configuring and monitoring the base DHCP snooping functionality.

hpicfDhcpSnoopOpt82Group.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopOpt82Group
hpicfDhcpSnoopOpt82Group.description: A collection of objects for configuring and monitoring DHCP snooping relay information option behavior.

hpicfDhcpSnoopServersGroup.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopServersGroup
hpicfDhcpSnoopServersGroup.description: A collection of objects for configuring and monitoring DHCP snooping trusted servers.

hpicfDhcpSnoopDbaseFileGroup.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopDbaseFileGroup
hpicfDhcpSnoopDbaseFileGroup.description: A collection of objects for configuring and monitoring DHCP snooping database file management.

hpicfDhcpSnoopBindingsGroup.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopBindingsGroup
hpicfDhcpSnoopBindingsGroup.description: A collection of objects for accessing the DHCP snooping lease database.

hpicfDhcpSnoopStaticBindingsGroup.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopStaticBindingsGroup
hpicfDhcpSnoopStaticBindingsGroup.description: A collection of objects for managing static configuration of IP source address bindings.

hpicfDhcpSnoopNotifyObjsGroup.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopNotifyObjsGroup
hpicfDhcpSnoopNotifyObjsGroup.description: Group of objects used in DHCP Snooping notifications.

hpicfDhcpSnoopPktsGroup.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopPktsGroup
hpicfDhcpSnoopPktsGroup.description: A collection of objects for monitoring the base DHCP snooping functionality.

hpicfDhcpSnoopClearStatsOptionsGroup.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopClearStatsOptionsGroup
hpicfDhcpSnoopClearStatsOptionsGroup.description: The MIB object represents the clear dhcp-snoop statistics information.

hpicfDhcpSnoopMaxbindingGroup.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopMaxbindingGroup
hpicfDhcpSnoopMaxbindingGroup.description: A collection of objects for configuring and monitoring DHCP snooping maxbinding.

hpicfDhcpSnoopPktsGroup1.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopPktsGroup1
hpicfDhcpSnoopPktsGroup1.description: A collection of objects for monitoring the base DHCP snooping functionality.

hpicfDhcpSnoopDbaseFileGroup1.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopDbaseFileGroup1
hpicfDhcpSnoopDbaseFileGroup1.description: A collection of objects for configuring and monitoring DHCP snooping database file management.

hpicfDhcpSnoopAllowOverwriteBindingGroup.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopAllowOverwriteBindingGroup
hpicfDhcpSnoopAllowOverwriteBindingGroup.description: The MIB object represents the DHCP Snooping allow-overwrite-binding information.

hpicfDhcpSnoopClearBindingsOptionsGroup.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopClearBindingsOptionsGroup
hpicfDhcpSnoopClearBindingsOptionsGroup.description: A collection of objects for clearing all the dynamic DHCP Snooping binding entries or selectively clearing entries based on the IP address, port or VLAN.

hpicfDhcpSnoopCompliance.name: hpicfDhcpSnoopCompliance
hpicfDhcpSnoopCompliance.description: The compliance statement for HP Routing switches that support DHCP Snooping.

hpicfDhcpSnoopCompliance2.description: The compliance statement for HP Routing switches that support DHCP Snooping.

hpicfDhcpSnoopCompliance3.description: The compliance statement for HP Routing switches that support DHCP Snooping.

hpicfDhcpSnoopCompliance4.description: The compliance statement for HP switches that support DHCP Snooping.

hpicfDhcpSnoopClearStatsCompliance.description: The compliance statement for clearing the dhcp-snooping Statistics implementation.

hpicfDhcpSnoopCompliance6.description: The compliance statement for HP Routing switches that support DHCP Snooping.

hpicfDhcpSnoopCompliance7.description: The compliance statement for HP switches that support DHCP Snooping.

hpicfDhcpSnoopCompliance8.description: The compliance statement for HP Routing switches that support DHCP Snooping.

hpicfDhcpSnoopCompliance9.description: The compliance statement for HP switches that support DHCP Snooping.
